        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:09PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over White Water Park, or
over Marietta. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marietta, Smyrna, Fair Oaks, White Water Park, Sandy Plains, Lost
Mountain Park, Dobbins Air Reserve Base, Jim R Miller Park, and
Mableton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
